### Function Responsibilities

- `EntryPoint.ps1`
  - top-level parameter block
  - calls `Start-Uninstaller`
  - exits with returned code
- `Start-Uninstaller.ps1`
  - orchestrates validation, discovery, matching, output, execution, and exit code
- `New-CompiledFilter.ps1`
  - validates and compiles filter definitions
- `Test-ApplicationMatch.ps1`
  - evaluates one application record against compiled filters
- `Get-UninstallRegistryPath.ps1`
  - builds machine/user registry descriptors
- `New-RegistryViewDescriptor.ps1`
  - expands one registry root into the correct view-specific
    descriptor records and stamps descriptor metadata
- `Get-InstalledApplication.ps1`
  - enumerates uninstall records and builds normalized application records
- `Format-RegistryPath.ps1`
  - formats the synthetic `RegistryPath` field and related
    registry path display text used by discovery warnings
- `Resolve-SidIdentity.ps1`
  - translates SID to username once per loaded user hive
- `Resolve-AppArchitecture.ps1`
  - computes `AppArch`
- `Resolve-UninstallString.ps1`
  - chooses `QuietUninstallString` vs `UninstallString`
- `Resolve-UninstallCommand.ps1`
  - parses supported uninstall command families
- `Invoke-SilentProcess.ps1`
  - launches, drains, waits, times out, and captures exit status
- `Format-OutputLine.ps1`
  - renders deterministic PDQ line output
- `ConvertTo-OutputFieldList.ps1`
  - builds the final ordered output field list

### External Seams

These functions exist primarily for testability and must stay thin:

- `Get-Is64BitOperatingSystem`
- `Get-LoadedUserRegistrySid`
- `Get-RegistryBaseKey`
- `Get-RegistrySubKey`
- `Get-RegistrySubKeyNames`
- `Get-RegistryValueNames`
- `Get-RegistryValue`
- `Resolve-SidIdentity`
- `Stop-ProcessTree`

## 13. Build System

### 13.1 Build Output Shape

`build.ps1` must emit a runnable script, not just concatenated function definitions.

Required build order:

1. `#Requires` and strict-mode setup
2. script-level attributes and `param()`
3. inlined string data, if used
4. private functions
5. public `Start-Uninstaller` function
6. terminal invocation:

```powershell
$RunResult = Start-Uninstaller @PSBoundParameters
$RunResult.Lines | & { process { Write-Output $PSItem } }
exit $RunResult.ExitCode
```

### 13.2 Strings Files

Use `.strings.psd1` only where a function has reusable user-facing messages.

Rules:

- no empty strings files
- build script inlines string data into the compiled artifact
- do not create strings files for ceremony only

## 14. Test Strategy

### 14.1 Test Layers

Use three layers:

1. Unit tests for pure helpers and filter logic
2. Orchestrator tests for `Start-Uninstaller` with mocked seam functions
3. Built-script integration tests that invoke `build/Start-Uninstaller.ps1` as a
   script and validate stdout plus exit code

### 14.2 Critical Unit Tests

- filter validation rejects missing `Property`
- filter validation rejects missing `Value`
- filter validation rejects invalid `MatchType`
- version operators reject non-`DisplayVersion`
- version operators reject non-version filter values
- `Simple` is case-insensitive exact
- `Wildcard` is case-insensitive wildcard
- `Regex` is case-insensitive culture-invariant regex
- version operators compare parsed `[version]`
- missing properties become non-match without throwing
- `DisplayVersion` string matching still works when version parsing fails
- `ConvertTo-NormalizedRegistryValue` handles:
  - `string`
  - numeric
  - `string[]`
  - unsupported types
- `Resolve-AppArchitecture` covers:
  - 32-bit OS short-circuit
  - x86 evidence
  - x64 evidence
  - `Program Files (x86)` precedence
  - tie -> `x86`
- `Resolve-UninstallCommand` covers:
  - MSI `/I -> /X`
  - quiet flag preservation
  - `/passive` detection
  - quoted EXE path
  - unquoted EXE path
  - `.cmd`
  - `.bat`
  - unsupported command
- `Invoke-SilentProcess` covers:
  - success
  - reboot-required
  - reboot-initiated
  - timeout
  - launch failure

### 14.3 Discovery Tests

- `HKLM` 32-bit and 64-bit path generation
- user SID filtering excludes `.DEFAULT`, `*_Classes`, and service SIDs
- SID resolution success and failure
- filter by `UserIdentityStatus = Unresolved`
- filter by exact `UserName`
- filter by `InstallScope = System`
- hidden entry exclusion by default
- hidden entry inclusion with `-IncludeHidden`
- nameless entry exclusion by default
- nameless entry inclusion with `-IncludeNameless`
- unreadable path warns and continues
- every registry open is read-only
- one registry record becomes one application record
- no dedupe

### 14.4 Orchestrator and Output Tests

- `-ListOnly` with one match -> exit `0`
- `-ListOnly` with no matches -> exit `1`
- uninstall mode with one success -> exit `0`
- uninstall mode with no matches -> exit `1`
- uninstall mode with multiple matches and no `-AllowMultipleMatches`:
  - no process launch
  - one blocked line per match
  - exit `2`
- uninstall mode with `-AllowMultipleMatches`:
  - deterministic order
  - per-entry lines emitted
  - aggregate exit `3` if any failure
- unsupported uninstall family -> `Failed`, exit `3`
- no uninstall string -> `Failed`, exit `3`
- timeout -> `TimedOut`, exit `3`
- `-Properties` raw values are emitted when present
- missing requested property emits `<null>`
- synthetic field in `-Properties` is a fatal validation error
- filter properties auto-append to output
- synthetic filter properties auto-append to output
- line output preserves:
  - mandatory fields first
  - additional fields after that
  - alphabetical field ordering
  - `<null>` handling
  - single-line sanitization

### 14.5 Built Script Integration Tests

The built artifact must be invoked as a script, not only dot-sourced.

Verify:

- top-level parameter binding works
- stdout lines are PDQ-friendly
- script exit codes match the spec
- build output has no syntax errors

## 15. Implementation Sequence

### Phase 0: Clean Up the Contract

- replace the current contradictory plan with this frozen contract
- update `build.ps1` expectations to build a runnable script
- update analyzer settings if needed

### Phase 1: External Seams and Shared Helpers

- create registry wrapper functions
- create SID resolution helper
- create process-tree stop helper
- create normalization/output helpers

Acceptance criteria:

- wrappers are tiny
- wrappers have focused tests
- no business logic is buried in a seam function

### Phase 2: Filter Engine

- implement `New-CompiledFilter`
- implement `Test-ApplicationMatch`
- implement `DisplayVersion` semantic operators

Acceptance criteria:

- all filter types pass direct tests
- invalid filter definitions fail fast

### Phase 3: Discovery Engine

- implement descriptor generation
- enumerate raw uninstall records
- normalize values
- stamp synthetic metadata
- apply hidden/nameless gates
- apply architecture filter

Acceptance criteria:

- all discovery records are deterministic
- all registry access is read-only
- user identity metadata is correct

### Phase 4: Uninstall Resolution and Execution

- implement uninstall string selection
- implement command parsing
- implement process launch, timeout, and tree kill
- map per-entry results

Acceptance criteria:

- every supported family parses correctly
- unsupported/no-command cases fail cleanly
- timeout behavior is deterministic

### Phase 5: Orchestrator and PDQ Output

- implement `Start-Uninstaller`
- enforce single-match default
- emit PDQ lines
- return script exit code

Acceptance criteria:

- line output format is stable
- multi-match block behavior is correct
- uninstall mode exits with the correct aggregate code

### Phase 6: Build, Integration, and Final Verification

- wire the top-level entrypoint into `build.ps1`
- run analyzer
- run full test suite
- invoke the built script directly in integration tests

Acceptance criteria:

- built script behaves correctly as a standalone PDQ artifact

## 16. Acceptance Checklist

- [ ] Build output is a runnable script with a top-level `param()` block.
- [ ] Script execution is non-interactive by default.
- [ ] Discovery searches `HKLM` plus loaded supported `HKU` user hives only.
- [ ] Hidden entries are excluded by default and included with `-IncludeHidden`.
- [ ] Nameless entries are excluded by default and included with `-IncludeNameless`.
- [ ] One registry record produces one application record.
- [ ] No dedupe exists anywhere in the rewrite.
- [ ] `Simple`, `Wildcard`, and `Regex` work case-insensitively.
- [ ] `DisplayVersion` supports `Simple`, `Wildcard`, `Regex`, `EQ`, `GT`, `GTE`,
      `LT`, and `LTE`.
- [ ] Version operators are rejected on non-`DisplayVersion` properties.
- [ ] Synthetic fields are valid for filtering.
- [ ] Synthetic fields are invalid in `-Properties`.
- [ ] Filter properties auto-append to output.
- [ ] Output field ordering is deterministic.
- [ ] Missing values emit as `<null>`.
- [ ] Output values are sanitized to single-line safe text.
- [ ] Default uninstall behavior blocks on more than one match.
- [ ] `-AllowMultipleMatches` enables deterministic multi-uninstall behavior.
- [ ] Supported uninstall families are MSI, EXE, `.cmd`, and `.bat`.
- [ ] Unsupported or missing uninstall commands fail the matched record.
- [ ] Timeout kills the full process tree.
- [ ] Exit codes `0`, `1`, `2`, `3`, and `4` behave exactly as documented.
- [ ] External dependency seams exist and are unit-testable.
- [ ] Integration tests invoke the built script directly and validate stdout plus
      exit code.
